{"title_page": "Ellingen (Prenzlau)", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=April 2015}}\n\n{{Infobox German location\n| type             = Village\n| name                    = Ellingen\n| image_photo             = Dorfkirche Ellingen (Prenzlau) 2018 SW.jpg\n| image_caption           = Village church\n| Town            = [[Prenzlau]]\n| district               = [[Uckermark (district)|Uckermark]]\n| Wappen              = \n| coordinates             = {{coord|53|20|56|N|13|49|55|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n| state              = Brandenburg\n| elevation                    = 25\n| area                  = 0.26\n| population               = 90\n| Stand                   = 2008\n| postal_code           = 17291\n| area_code                = 039853\n| Lagekarte               = \n| Lagekarte-Beschreibung  = \n}}\n\n'''Ellingen''' is a small village in the northeast of the federated state of [[Brandenburg]], [[Germany]].  The village is part of the [[Dedelow]] [[Ortsteil|section (''Ortsteil'')]] of the city of [[Prenzlau]], in the [[Districts of Germany|District (''Landkreis'')]] of [[Uckermark]]. With just 90 inhabitants, it is one of the smallest villages in [[Prenzlau]].<ref>[http://www.prenzlau.eu/cms/detail.php/land_bb_boa_01.c.157478.de Ellingen auf prenzlau.eu]</ref>\n\n==History==\nEllingen was first mentioned in 1285 as owned by \"Otto of Ellinge\". Slavic settlements preceded the village's founding. During the Middle Ages, Ellingen belonged to the Arnim family. Later, the village came into the possession of the city of Prenzlau. In 1961, the village of Ellingen was incorporated in the Dedelow section of Prenzlau.<ref>[http://www.brandenburg.de/sixcms/media.php/4055/Beitrag19.15_Landkreis73_HistorischesGemeindeverzeichnis2005.pdf Historisches Gemeindeverzeichnis des Landes Brandenburg] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131026041401/http://www.brandenburg.de/sixcms/media.php/4055/Beitrag19.15_Landkreis73_HistorischesGemeindeverzeichnis2005.pdf |date=2013-10-26 }} (PDF; 386&nbsp;kB)</ref>\n\n== References ==\n<references/>\n\n[[Category:Villages in Brandenburg]]\n[[Category:Bezirk Neubrandenburg]]\n", "text_old": "{{Orphan|date=April 2015}}\n\n{{Infobox German location\n| type             = Village\n| name                    = Ellingen\n| image_photo             = Dorfkirche Ellingen (Prenzlau) 2018 SW.jpg\n| image_caption           = Village church\n| Ortsteil                = [[Dedelow]]\n| Town            = [[Prenzlau]]\n| district               = [[Uckermark (district)|Uckermark]]\n| Alternativanzeige-Gemeindename = \n| Ortswappen              = \n| Ortswappen-Beschreibung = \n| coordinates             = {{coord|53|20|56|N|13|49|55|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n| state              = Brandenburg\n| elevation                    = 25\n| area                  = 0.26\n| population               = 90\n| Stand                   = 2008\n| postal_code           = 17291\n| Postleitzahl2           = \n| area_code                = 039853\n| Vorwahl2                = \n| Lagekarte               = \n| Lagekarte-Beschreibung  = \n}}\n\n'''Ellingen''' is a small village in the northeast of the federated state of [[Brandenburg]], [[Germany]].  The village is a [[Gemeinde (Germany)|subdivision (''Gemeinde'')]] of the [[Dedelow]] [[Ortsteil|section (''Ortsteil'')]] of the city of [[Prenzlau]], in the [[Districts of Germany|District (''Landkreis'')]] of [[Uckermark]]. With just 90 inhabitants, it is one of the smallest villages in [[Prenzlau]].<ref>[http://www.prenzlau.eu/cms/detail.php/land_bb_boa_01.c.157478.de Ellingen auf prenzlau.eu]</ref>\n\n==History==\nEllingen was first mentioned in 1285 as owned by \"Otto of Ellinge\". Slavic settlements preceded the village's founding. During the Middle Ages, Ellingen belonged to the Arnim family. Later, the village came into the possession of the city of Prenzlau. In 1961, the village of Ellingen was incorporated in the Dedelow section of Prenzlau.<ref>[http://www.brandenburg.de/sixcms/media.php/4055/Beitrag19.15_Landkreis73_HistorischesGemeindeverzeichnis2005.pdf Historisches Gemeindeverzeichnis des Landes Brandenburg] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131026041401/http://www.brandenburg.de/sixcms/media.php/4055/Beitrag19.15_Landkreis73_HistorischesGemeindeverzeichnis2005.pdf |date=2013-10-26 }} (PDF; 386&nbsp;kB)</ref>\n\n== References ==\n<references/>\n\n[[Category:Villages in Brandenburg]]\n[[Category:Bezirk Neubrandenburg]]\n", "name_user": "Markussep", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ellingen_(Prenzlau)"}
