our friends in France as you fight this devastating fire. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190415225212/https://twitter.com/JustinTrudeau/status/1117872005724852224 |archive-date=15 April 2019 |url-status=live}}{{Primary source inline|date=April 2019}}</ref> President of the United States [[Donald Trump]],<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.cnn.com/world/live-news/notre-dame-fire/h_27494efb1996ed06048054ccf19d283e |title=President Trump on the 'terrible, terrible fire' |date=15 April 2019 |publisher=CNN |accessdate=15 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefings-statements/statement-press-secretary-cathedral-notre-dame-de-paris/ |date=16 April 2019 |title=Statement by the Press Secretary on the Cathedral of Notre Dame de Paris |work=[[The White House]] |accessdate=19 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190419192945/https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefings-statements/statement-press-secretary-cathedral-notre-dame-de-paris/ |archive-date=19 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> President of the People's Republic of China [[Xi Jinping]],<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/europe/2019-04/16/c_137982309.htm |title=Xi sends condolence to Macron over Notre Dame fire |date=16 April 2019 |publisher=Xinhua News Agency |accessdate=16 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416145117/http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/europe/2019-04/16/c_137982309.htm |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> President of Russia [[Vladimir Putin]],<ref>{{cite news |url=http://en.kremlin.ru/events/president/news/60300 |title=Message to Emmanuel Macron |date=16 April 2019 |publisher=Russian Presidential Executive Office |accessdate=16 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416103822/http://en.kremlin.ru/events/president/news/60300 |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> President of Israel [[Reuven Rivlin]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesofisrael.com/president-rivlin-offers-solidarity-with-france-as-notre-dame-burns/ |title=President Rivlin offers solidarity with France as Notre Dame burns |website=[[The Times of Israel]] |accessdate=15 April 2019}}</ref> King of Bahrain [[Hamad bin Isa Al Khalifa]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://gulfdailynews.net/bahrain/hm-king-offers-solidarity-with-france/ |title=HM King offers solidarity with France |work=Gulf Daily News |date=16 April 2019 |accessdate=16 April 2019}}</ref> Prime Minister of Australia [[Scott Morrison]], King [[Mohammed VI of Morocco]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2019-04/16/c_137979897.htm |title=Morocco king vows solidarity with France following Notre Dame Cathedral fire |publisher=Xinhua News Agency |date=16 April 2019 |accessdate=16 April 2019}}</ref> President of Egypt [[Abdel Fattah el-Sisi]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.egypttoday.com/Article/1/68369/Sisi-expresses-solidarity-with-France-over-Paris-cathedral-fire |title=Sisi expresses solidarity with France over Paris cathedral fire |date=15 April 2019 |work=Egypt Today |accessdate=16 April 2019 |agency=MENA}}</ref> President of Latvia [[Raimonds V\u0113jonis]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://eng.lsm.lv/article/politics/diplomacy/bells-ring-out-in-riga-in-support-of-france-and-notre-dame.a316170/ |title=Bells ring out in R\u012bga in support of France and Notre Dame |date=16 April 2019 |publisher=[[Public Broadcasting of Latvia]] |accessdate=16 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190418160108/https://eng.lsm.lv/article/politics/diplomacy/bells-ring-out-in-riga-in-support-of-france-and-notre-dame.a316170/ |archive-date=18 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> President of Ghana [[Nana Akufo-Addo]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.graphic.com.gh/news/general-news/notre-dame-cathedral-fire-akufo-addo-comiserates-with-france.html |title=Notre Dame Cathedral fire: Akufo-Addo commiserates with France |date=16 April 2019 |website=Graphic Online |url-status=live |accessdate=17 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416132407/https://www.graphic.com.gh/news/general-news/notre-dame-cathedral-fire-akufo-addo-comiserates-with-france.html |archive-date=16 April 2019}}</ref> President of Belarus [[Alexander Lukashenko]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://president.gov.by/en/news_en/view/condolences-to-france-president-emmanuel-macron-20896/ |title=Condolences to France President Emmanuel Macron |date=16 April 2019 |website=President of the Republic of Belarus |accessdate=19 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190419061427/http://president.gov.by/en/news_en/view/condolences-to-france-president-emmanuel-macron-20896/ |archive-date=19 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> and the President of the Republic of China (Taiwan) [[Tsai Ing-wen]].<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://twitter.com/iingwen/status/1117981036783083520|title=Tsai Ing-wen (@iingwen)|website=Twitter|date=15 April 2019|accessdate=21 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190418084152/https://twitter.com/iingwen/status/1117981036783083520|archive-date=18 April 2019|url-status=live}}{{Primary source inline|date=April 2019}}</ref> |name=|}} extended condolences.\n\nThrough the night of the fire and into the next day, people gathered along the Seine to hold vigils, sing and pray.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-france-notredame-scene/in-the-heart-of-paris-a-wounded-notre-dame-stirs-emotions-idUSKCN1RS15K |title=In the heart of Paris, a wounded Notre-Dame stirs emotions |first1=Matthias |last1=Blamont |first2=Geert |last2=de Clercq |date=16 April 2019 |accessdate=16 April 2019 |work=[[Reuters]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416124316/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-france-notredame-scene/in-the-heart-of-paris-a-wounded-notre-dame-stirs-emotions-idUSKCN1RS15K |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/global/video/2019/apr/16/parisians-sing-hymns-as-they-watch-notre-dame-burning-video |title=Parisians sing hymns as they watch Notre Dame burning \u2013 video |agency=Reuters/AP |date=16 April 2019 |work=The Guardian |accessdate=17 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416110006/https://www.theguardian.com/global/video/2019/apr/16/parisians-sing-hymns-as-they-watch-notre-dame-burning-video |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/notre-dame-cathedral-fire-paris-stunning-video-shows-people-singing-hymn-to-honor-notre-dame-as-it-burned/ |title=Stunning video shows people singing hymn to honor Notre Dame as it burned |first=Danielle |last=Garrand |date=16 April 2019 |website=CBS News |accessdate=22 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416103235/https://www.cbsnews.com/news/notre-dame-cathedral-fire-paris-stunning-video-shows-people-singing-hymn-to-honor-notre-dame-as-it-burned/ |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe following Sunday at [[Saint-Eustache, Paris|Saint-Eustache Church]], the Archbishop of Paris, [[Michel Aupetit]], honoured the firefighters with the presentation of a book of scriptures saved from the fire.<ref>{{cite news |title=Paris Easter Mass honors firefighters who saved Notre Dame |first=Angela |last=Charlton |date=21 April 2019 |accessdate=25 April 2019 |url=https://apnews.com/edd07fca7fa74601aacb8e2592698ae5 |website=AP News}}</ref>\n\n== Investigation ==\n[[File:Notre-Dame en feu, 20h06.jpg|thumb|upright=1.2|left|The fire seen from [[Pont de la Tournelle]] ]]\nOn 16 April, the Paris prosecutor said there was no evidence of a deliberate act.<ref name=\"forest\" />\n\nThe fire has been compared to the similar [[1992 Windsor Castle fire]] and the [[Uppark#Fire|Uppark fire]], among others,<ref name=\"monde20190416\">{{cite news |last1=Damg\u00e9 |first1=Mathilde |last2=Dagorn |first2=Gary |last3=Durand |first3=Anne-A\u00ebl |title=Nantes, Lun\u00e9ville, Windsor... les derniers grands incendies de b\u00e2timents historiques |url=https://www.lemonde.fr/les-decodeurs/article/2019/04/16/nantes-luneville-windsor-les-derniers-grands-incendies-de-batiments-historiques_5451131_4355770.html |accessdate=17 April 2019 |work=Le Monde |date=16 April 2019 |language=fr |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190417092520/https://www.lemonde.fr/les-decodeurs/article/2019/04/16/nantes-luneville-windsor-les-derniers-grands-incendies-de-batiments-historiques_5451131_4355770.html |archive-date=17 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> and has raised old questions about the safety of similar structures and the techniques used to restore them.<ref name=\"monde20190416\" />\nRenovation works [[Construction and renovation fires|increase fire risk]], and a police source reported they are looking into whether such work had caused this incident.<ref name=\"six_questions\" /><ref>{{cite news |last1=Captain |first1=Sean |title=Notre-Dame fire: Why historic restorations keep going up in flames |url=https://www.fastcompany.com/90335390/notre-dame-fire-why-historic-restorations-keep-going-up-in-flames |work=Fast Company |date=15 April 2019 |accessdate=16 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416193655/https://www.fastcompany.com/90335390/notre-dame-fire-why-historic-restorations-keep-going-up-in-flames |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe renovations presented a fire risk from sparks, [[Short circuit|short-circuits]], and heat from welding (roof repairs involved cutting, and welding lead sheets resting on timber<ref name=\"six_questions\" />). Normally, no electrical installations were allowed in the roof space due to the extreme fire risk.<ref name=\"forest\" />\nThe roof framing was of very dry timber, often powdery with age.<ref name=\"six_questions\" /> After the fire the architect responsible for fire safety at the cathedral acknowledged that the rate at which fire might spread had been underestimated, and experts said it was well known that a fire in the roof would be almost impossible to control.<ref name=\"nytimes20190419\" />\n\nOf the firms working on the restoration,<ref name=\"time-lapse\" /> a ''[[Scaffolding|Europe Echafaudage]]'' team was the only one working there on the day of the fire; the company said no soldering or welding was underway before the fire. The scaffolding was receiving electrical supply for temporary elevators and lighting.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nouvelobs.com/societe/20190418.OBS11772/notre-dame-les-echafaudeurs-livrent-leur-version-des-faits.html |title=Notre-Dame: les \u00e9chafaudeurs livrent leur version des faits |work=L'Obs |date=18 April 2019 |language=fr |accessdate=23 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190418143623/https://www.nouvelobs.com/societe/20190418.OBS11772/notre-dame-les-echafaudeurs-livrent-leur-version-des-faits.html |archive-date=18 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |first=Oliver |last=Rowland |date=17 April 2019 |url=https://www.connexionfrance.com/French-news/Alarms-on-spire-scaffolding-did-not-go-off |title=Alarms on spire scaffolding did not go off |work=The Connexion |accessdate=23 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190419232357/https://www.connexionfrance.com/French-news/Alarms-on-spire-scaffolding-did-not-go-off |archive-date=19 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"april19rescue\" />\nLe Bras Fr\u00e8res<ref>[http://www.le-bras-freres.com/ Le Bras Fr\u00e8res] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190131123604/http://www.le-bras-freres.com/ |date=31 January 2019}}, a company specialized in roofing including for heritage roofing restoration.</ref> said it had followed procedure and that none of its personnel were on site when the fire broke out.<ref name=\"reuters damage\" /> [[Time-lapse]] images taken by a camera installed by them showed smoke first rising from the base of the spire.<ref name=\"time-lapse\">{{cite news |last1=Rose |first1=Michael |last2=Carriat |first2=Julie |title=Time-lapse shots of Notre-Dame spire may offer clues on blaze |url=https://reuters.com/article/france-notredame/time-lapse-shots-of-notre-dame-spire-may-offer-clues-on-blaze-idINL5N21Z69N |accessdate=18 April 2019 |work=Reuters |date=18 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190419080659/https://www.reuters.com/article/france-notredame/time-lapse-shots-of-notre-dame-spire-may-offer-clues-on-blaze-idINL5N21Z69N |archive-date=19 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 April, the structure was considered safe enough for entry of investigators, who unofficially stated that they were considering theories involving malfunction of electric [[Bell-ringer|bell-ringing]] apparatus, and cigarette butts discovered on the renovation scaffolding.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Nossiter |first1=Adam |title=Notre-Dame Fire Investigators Focus on Short-Circuit and Cigarettes |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/25/world/europe/notre-dame-fire-investigation.html |accessdate=28 April 2019 |work=The New York Times |date=25 April 2019}}</ref> Le Bras Fr\u00e8res (the roofing company) confirmed its workers had smoked cigarettes, contrary to regulations, but denied that a cigarette butt could have started the fire.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.france24.com/en/20190626-france-paris-notre-dame-fire-no-sign-criminal-cause-prosecutors-probe-negligence |title=No sign of criminal cause in Notre-Dame fire, prosecutors say |accessdate=24 July 2019 |work=France24 |date=26 June 2019}}</ref> The Paris prosecutor's office announced on 26 June that no evidence had been found to suggest a criminal motive.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Ganley |first1=Elaine |title=There Is No Sign That the Notre Dame Fire Was of Criminal Origin, the Paris Prosecutor Says |url=https://time.com/5615294/notre-dame-fire-criminal-investigation/ |accessdate=24 July 2019 |work=The New York Times |date=27 June 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe security employee monitoring the alarm system was new on the job, and was on a second eight-hour shift that day because his relief had not arrived. Additionally, the fire security system used confusing terminology in its referencing parts of the cathedral, which contributed to the initial confusion as to the location of the fire.<ref name=\"nytimes 20190719\" />\n\nAs of September, five months after the fire, investigators thought the cause of the fire was more likely an electrical fault than a cigarette. Determining the exact place in which the fire started was expected to take a great deal more time and work.<ref name=\"5moUpdate\">{{cite web |last1=Richman-Abdou |first1=Kelly |title=Notre-Dame Updates: What We Know About the Cathedral Five Months After the Fire |url=https://mymodernmet.com/notre-dame-fire-updates/ |website=My Modern Met |language=en |date=10 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Reconstruction ==\n[[File:Chartres roof space the Charpente de Fer.jpg|upright=1.2|thumb|left|[[Chartres Cathedral]] was rebuilt with wrought iron trusses and copper sheeting after an 1836 fire.<ref>{{cite web |title=Chartres Cathedral \u2013 Cath\u00e9drale Notre-Dame de Chartres |url=https://chartrescathedral.net/ |accessdate=18 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190417033837/https://chartrescathedral.net/ |archive-date=17 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>]]\nOn the night of the fire Macron said that the cathedral, which is owned by the state, would be rebuilt, and launched an international fundraising campaign.<ref name=\"gutted\" /><ref name=\"bbc\" /><ref name=\"ap-latest\">{{cite web |url=https://www.apnews.com/91d9711a9e5549109dd04d264e02b720 |title=The Latest: French leader vows to rebuild damaged Notre Dame |date=15 April 2019 |website=AP News |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190415215922/https://apnews.com/91d9711a9e5549109dd04d264e02b720 |archive-date=15 April 2019 |url-status=live |accessdate=15 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/apr/15/notre-dame-fire-paris-france-cathedral |title=Notre Dame fire: Macron pledges to rebuild devastated Paris cathedral |first1=Angelique |last1=Chrisafis |first2=Jon |last2=Henley |date=16 April 2019 |work=The Guardian |accessdate=16 April 2019 |issn=0261-3077 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416000607/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/apr/15/notre-dame-fire-paris-france-cathedral |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=The Notre Dame Cathedral will rise again, French President Emmanuel Macron promises |url=https://eu.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2019/04/15/notre-dame-cathedral-whats-next-rebuild-emmanuel-macron/3479116002/ |accessdate=16 April 2019 |newspaper=[[USA Today]] |first=Kristin |last=Lam |date=15 April 2019}}</ref>\nFrance's cathedrals have been owned by the state since 1905,<ref name=\"FT\">{{cite news |title=Macron says he wants Notre-Dame rebuilt in 5 years |first1=Victor |last1=Mallet |first2=Harriet |last2=Agnew |url=https://www.ft.com/content/62ac5270-6015-11e9-b285-3acd5d43599e |date=16 April 2019 |website=Financial Times |accessdate=24 April 2019}}</ref> and are not privately insured.<ref name=\"FT\" /><ref name=\"cbs insured\">{{cite web |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/notre-dame-cathedral-rebuild-in-paris-could-take-40-years/ |title=Why an expert says it could take 40 years to rebuild Notre Dame |first=Haley |last=Ott |date=16 April 2019 |accessdate=17 April 2019 |website=[[CBS News]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416172154/https://www.cbsnews.com/news/notre-dame-cathedral-rebuild-in-paris-could-take-40-years/ |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The heritage conservation organisation [[:fr:Fondation du patrimoine|Fondation du Patrimoine]] estimated the damage in the hundreds of millions of [[euro]]s;<ref name=\"reuters damage\">{{cite web |url=https://ca.reuters.com/article/topNews/idCAKCN1RS0AV-OCATP |title=No sign of arson in Notre-Dame blaze as nation grieves for symbol |first1=Richard |last1=Lough |first2=Elizabeth |last2=Pineau |agency=publisher |date=16 April 2019 |accessdate=16 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416142339/https://ca.reuters.com/article/topNews/idCAKCN1RS0AV-OCATP |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref> but, according to President Robert Leblanc,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fondationavenirpatrimoineparis.fr/nous-connaitre/notre-organisation-fondation-patrimoine/ |title=Our organization |publisher=Fondation Avenir du Patrimoine \u00e0 Paris |accessdate=24 April 2019}}</ref> losses from the fire are not expected to substantially impact the private insurance industry.<ref name=\"FT\" /><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-04-17/france-s-axa-insured-notre-dame-artwork-two-construction-firms |title=France's Axa Insured Notre Dame Art, Two Construction Firms |first=Katherine |last=Chiglinsky |date=17 April 2019 |accessdate=24 April 2019 |url-access=limited |publisher=[[Bloomberg News]]}}</ref>\n\nEuropean art insurers stated the cost would be similar to ongoing renovations of the [[Palace of Westminster]] in London, which currently is estimated around \u20ac7{{nbsp}}billion.<ref name=\"reuters insurance\">{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-france-notredame-insurance/insurers-expect-france-to-bear-notre-dame-rebuilding-cost-idUSKCN1RS1LO |title=Insurers expect France to bear Notre-Dame rebuilding cost |first1=Noor Zainab |last1=Hussain |first2=Paul |last2=Arnold |date=16 April 2019 |accessdate=16 April 2019 |work=[[Reuters]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416193024/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-france-notredame-insurance/insurers-expect-france-to-bear-notre-dame-rebuilding-cost-idUSKCN1RS1LO |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nThis cost does not include damage to any of the artwork or artefacts within the cathedral; art insurers said any pieces on loan from other museums would have been insured, but the works owned by the cathedral would not have been insurable.<ref name=\"reuters insurance\" />\nWhile Macron hoped the cathedral could be restored in time for the [[2024 Summer Olympics|2024 Paris Summer Olympics]], architects expect the work could take from twenty to forty years, as any new structure would need to balance restoring the look of the original building, using wood and stone sourced from the same regions used in the original construction, with the structural reinforcement required for preventing a similar disaster in the future.<ref name=\"cbs insured\" /><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2019/04/16/notre-dame-cathedral-whats-next-rebuild-emmanuel-macron/3482371002/ |title=Why Notre Dame didn't completely crumble in the blaze. And why it could take decades to repair. |first3=Kristin |last3=Lam |first1=Ryan W. |last1=Miller |first2=Doyle |last2=Rice |date=17 April 2019 |accessdate=23 April 2019 |work=[[USA Today]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190420204712/https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2019/04/16/notre-dame-cathedral-whats-next-rebuild-emmanuel-macron/3482371002/ |archive-date=20 April 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nThere is discussion of whether to reconstruct the cathedral in modified form.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-france-notredame-arcelormittal-idUSKCN1RU0V2 |last=Kar-Gupta |first=Sudip |last2=Lough |first2=Richard |date=18 April 2019 |title=Steelmaker ArcelorMittal to offer steel for Notre-Dame Cathedral restoration |work=[[Reuters]] |accessdate=18 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190418094802/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-france-notredame-arcelormittal-idUSKCN1RU0V2 |archive-date=18 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\nRebuilding the roof with titanium sheets and steel trusses has been suggested;<ref>{{cite news |last1=Jackson |first1=Patrick |title=How new tech might help Notre-Dame rebuild |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-47971914 |date=18 April 2019 |website=BBC News |accessdate=18 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190418173230/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-47971914 |archive-date=18 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\nother options include rebuilding in the original lead and wood,<ref name=\"cbs insured\" /> rebuilding with modern materials not visible from the outside (like the reinforced concrete trusses at [[Reims Cathedral]]),<ref name=\"april19rescue\" /><ref>{{cite news |last1=Silverstein |first1=Hannah |last2=Camerlenghi |first2=Nicola |title=After the Fire, a 21st-Century Notre Dame |url=https://news.dartmouth.edu/news/2019/04/after-fire-21st-century-notre-dame |work=Dartmouth News |date=18 April 2019 |accessdate=22 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190420195317/https://news.dartmouth.edu/news/2019/04/after-fire-21st-century-notre-dame |archive-date=20 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> or a combination of restored old elements and newly designed ones.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Clarke |first1=Joseph L. |title=Opinion: The reconstruction of Notre-Dame is not the only answer |url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/opinion/article-the-reconstruction-of-notre-dame-is-not-the-only-answer/ |work=[[The Globe and Mail]] |accessdate=18 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190418183215/https://www.theglobeandmail.com/opinion/article-the-reconstruction-of-notre-dame-is-not-the-only-answer/ |archive-date=18 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Notre-Dame bach\u00e9e.jpg|upright=2.8|thumb|right|White [[tarpaulin]]s over metal beams were quickly rigged to protect the interior from the elements. Nettings protect the destabilised exterior.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Nossiter |first1=Adam |title=Notre-Dame, Ravaged by Fire, Faces a New Threat: Rain |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/23/world/europe/notre-dame-fire-protect.html |work=The New York Times |date=23 April 2019 |url-access=limited}}</ref>]]\nFrench prime minister [[\u00c9douard Philippe]] announced an [[architectural design competition]] for a new spire \"adapted to the techniques and the challenges of our era.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.euronews.com/2019/04/15/fire-underway-at-notre-dame-cathedral-in-paris-firefighters-say |title=Notre Dame fire: Global contest launched to design new spire for blaze-hit cathedral |date=18 April 2019 |first1=Emma |last1=Beswick |first2=Cristina |last2=Abellan Matamoros |website=[[Euronews]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190415221945/https://www.euronews.com/2019/04/15/fire-underway-at-notre-dame-cathedral-in-paris-firefighters-say |archive-date=15 April 2019 |url-status=live |accessdate=24 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Notre Dame Fire: France Is Holding an International Competition for Architects to Design the Cathedral's New Spire |website=Newsweek |first=Brendan |last=Cole |url=https://www.newsweek.com/notre-dame-france-holding-international-competition-architects-design-1399017 |date=17 April 2019 |accessdate=24 April 2019}}</ref> The [[Notre-Dame de Paris#Projected restoration of the spire|spire replacement project]] has gathered a variety of designs and some controversy, particularly its legal exemption from environmental and heritage rules.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Marshall |first1=Alex |title=Glass, Golden Flames or a Beam of Light: What Should Replace Notre-Dame's Spire? |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/05/10/arts/design/notre-dame-spire-designs.html |work=The New York Times |date=10 May 2019 |url-access=limited}}</ref> After the design competition was announced, the French senate amended the government's restoration bill to require the roof to be restored to how it was before the fire. This amendment awaits approval by the National Assembly of France.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/notre-dame-cathedral-roof-fire-design-competition-paris-france-a8968791.html |title=Notre Dame design competition seeks new roof for world famous Paris cathedral |last=James |first=Liam |date=21 Jun 2019 |work=Independent |accessdate=26 June 2019}}</ref> On 16 July, 95 days after the fire that destroyed the cathedral's roof and central spire, the law that will govern the restoration of the cathedral was finally approved by the French parliament. It recognises its UNESCO World Heritage Site status and the need to respect existing international charters and practices, to \"preserve the historic, artistic and architectural history of the monument\", and to limit any derogations to the existing heritage, planning, environmental and construction codes to a minimum.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theartnewspaper.com/analysis/it-s-official-the-new-notre-dame-will-look-like-the-old-notre-dame |last=Bandarin |first=Francesco |date=2 August 2019 |title=It\u2019s official: the new Notre Dame will look like the old Notre Dame |work=[[The Art Newspaper]] |accessdate=5 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Fundraising ===\n{{As of|2019|04|22}}, donations of over \u20ac1{{nbsp}}billion have been pledged for the cathedral's reconstruction,<ref>{{cite news |title=Notre Dame fire was a warning bell. But will Europe listen? |first=Raf |last=Casert |website=AP News |date=22 April 2019 |url=https://apnews.com/9d791857100b4eabb9f63a32a1c4cdaf |accessdate=23 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190423073824/https://www.apnews.com/9d791857100b4eabb9f63a32a1c4cdaf |archive-date=23 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> at least \u20ac880{{nbsp}}million of that in less than a day after Macron's appeal.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://time.com/5571518/notre-dame-donations/ |work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]] |first=Ciara |last=Nugent |title=Pledges Reach Almost $1 Billion To Rebuild Paris' Notre Dame Cathedral |date=17 April 2019 |accessdate=23 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190423151848/http://time.com/5571518/notre-dame-donations/ |archive-date=23 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\nPledges \u20ac10M and over include:\n{{div col|colwidth=18em|content=\n* [[Bernard Arnault|Arnault]] family & [[LVMH]] (\u20ac200M)<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-france-notredame-arnault/billionaire-arnaults-family-and-lvmh-to-donate-200-mln-euros-for-paris-notre-dame-idUSKCN1RS0H8 |title=Billionaire Arnault's family and LVMH to donate 200 mln euros for Paris' Notre-Dame |date=16 April 2019 |accessdate=16 April 2019 |work=[[Reuters]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416065656/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-france-notredame-arnault/billionaire-arnaults-family-and-lvmh-to-donate-200-mln-euros-for-paris-notre-dame-idUSKCN1RS0H8 |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Liliane Bettencourt|Bettencourt]] family & [[L'Or\u00e9al]] (\u20ac200M)<ref>{{cite web |title=Notre-Dame: LVMH et la famille Arnault annoncent un 'don de 200 millions d'euros' |url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/flash-eco/notre-dame-lvmh-et-la-famille-arnault-annoncent-un-don-de-200-millions-d-euros-20190416 |website=[[Le Figaro]] |date=16 April 2019 |language=fr |accessdate=16 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416071632/http://www.lefigaro.fr/flash-eco/notre-dame-lvmh-et-la-famille-arnault-annoncent-un-don-de-200-millions-d-euros-20190416 |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Fran\u00e7ois Pinault|Pinault]] family & [[Groupe Art\u00e9mis|Art\u00e9mis]] (\u20ac100M)<ref>{{cite web |title=Incendie \u00e0 Notre-Dame: la famille Pinault d\u00e9bloque 100 millions d'euros |url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/flash-actu/notre-dame-de-paris-la-famille-pinault-debloque-100-millions-d-euros-20190416 |website=[[Le Figaro]] |date=16 April 2019 |language=fr |accessdate=17 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190417095409/http://www.lefigaro.fr/flash-actu/notre-dame-de-paris-la-famille-pinault-debloque-100-millions-d-euros-20190416 |archive-date=17 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Total S.A.|Total SA]] (\u20ac100M)<ref>{{cite web |title=France-Total fait un don de 100 millions d'euros pour Notre-Dame de Paris |url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/flash-eco/france-total-fait-un-don-de-100-millions-d-euros-pour-notre-dame-de-paris-20190416 |work=[[Le Figaro]] |date=16 April 2019 |accessdate=16 April 2019 |language=fr |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416120814/http://www.lefigaro.fr/flash-eco/france-total-fait-un-don-de-100-millions-d-euros-pour-notre-dame-de-paris-20190416 |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n* Paris city government (\u20ac50M)<ref>{{cite news |title=Notre-Dame: la mairie de Paris d\u00e9bloque 50 millions d'euros |date=16 April 2019 |url=http://www.courrier-picard.fr/178003/article/2019-04-16/notre-dame-la-mairie-de-paris-debloque-50-millions-deuros |website=courrier-picard.fr |language=fr |accessdate=23 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416123425/http://www.courrier-picard.fr/178003/article/2019-04-16/notre-dame-la-mairie-de-paris-debloque-50-millions-deuros |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Cagnottelemonde2\">{{cite web |title=Notre-Dame de Paris: cagnottes, promesses de dons et souscription nationale pour financer la reconstruction |url=https://www.lemonde.fr/societe/article/2019/04/16/notre-dame-les-cagnottes-se-multiplient-et-macron-annonce-une-souscription-nationale_5450645_3224.html |work=Le Monde |date=16 April 2019 |accessdate=16 April 2019 |language=fr |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416035552/https://www.lemonde.fr/societe/article/2019/04/16/notre-dame-les-cagnottes-se-multiplient-et-macron-annonce-une-souscription-nationale_5450645_3224.html |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[BNP Paribas]] SA (\u20ac20M)<ref>{{cite news |title=BNP Paribas, SocGen Join Notre Dame Donor List as Pledges Exceed $790 Million |first=Cristina |last=Roca |date=17 April 2019 |url=https://www.marketscreener.com/BNP-PARIBAS-4618/news/BNP-Paribas-SocGen-Join-Notre-Dame-Donor-List-as-Pledges-Exceed-790-Million-28437868/ |website=Market Screener |agency=Dow Jones |accessdate=23 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190417120827/https://www.marketscreener.com/BNP-PARIBAS-4618/news/BNP-Paribas-SocGen-Join-Notre-Dame-Donor-List-as-Pledges-Exceed-790-Million-28437868/?utm_medium=RSS&utm_content=20190417 |archive-date=17 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Jean-Claude Decaux|Decaux]] family & [[JCDecaux]] (\u20ac20M)<ref>{{cite web |title=Le secteur priv\u00e9 promet pr\u00e8s de 700 millions d'euros pour reconstruire Notre-Dame |url=https://www.boursorama.com/actualite-economique/actualites/le-secteur-prive-promet-pres-de-700-millions-d-euros-pour-reconstruire-notre-dame-2dd239e4d8c0d278d0c6425acf2a02bc |website=Boursorama |agency=Agence France-Presse (AFP) |date=16 April 2019 |accessdate=16 April 2019 |language=fr |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416162533/https://www.boursorama.com/actualite-economique/actualites/le-secteur-prive-promet-pres-de-700-millions-d-euros-pour-reconstruire-notre-dame-2dd239e4d8c0d278d0c6425acf2a02bc |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[AXA]] SA (\u20ac10M)<ref>{{cite press release |url=https://www.axa.com/fr/newsroom/communiques-de-presse/axa-s-associe-a-l-elan-de-solidarite-apres-l-incendie-de-notre-dame-de-paris |title=AXA s'associe \u00e0 l'\u00e9lan de solidarit\u00e9 apr\u00e8s l'incendie de Notre-Dame de Paris |publisher=AXA |date=16 April 2019 |language=fr}}</ref>\n* [[Lily Safra]] (\u20ac10M)<ref>{{cite web |title=Plus de 800 millions d'euros de dons pour la reconstruction de Notre-Dame |date=16 April 2019 |url=https://www.dna.fr/actualite/2019/04/16/les-promesses-de-dons-affluent-pour-la-reconstruction-de-notre-dame |website=[[Les Derni\u00e8res Nouvelles d'Alsace]] |accessdate=23 April 2019 |language=fr |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416113934/https://www.dna.fr/actualite/2019/04/16/les-promesses-de-dons-affluent-pour-la-reconstruction-de-notre-dame |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Martin Bouygues|Bouygues]] family (\u20ac10M)<ref>{{cite web |language=fr-FR |title=Entreprises et grandes fortunes se mobilisent pour la reconstruction de Notre-Dame |work=[[La Croix]] |date=16 April 2019 |issn=0242-6056 |url=https://www.la-croix.com/Economie/Entreprises-grandes-fortunes-mobilisent-reconstruction-Notre-Dame-2019-04-16-1301016005 |accessdate=16 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416120223/https://www.la-croix.com/Economie/Entreprises-grandes-fortunes-mobilisent-reconstruction-Notre-Dame-2019-04-16-1301016005 |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Marc Ladreit de Lacharri\u00e8re|De Lacharri\u00e8re]] family & [[FIMALAC]] (\u20ac10M)<ref name=\"Cagnottelemonde2\" />\n* [[\u00cele-de-France]] (\u20ac10M)<ref name=\"Cagnottelemonde2\" />\n* [[Soci\u00e9t\u00e9 G\u00e9n\u00e9rale]] (\u20ac10M)<ref name=\"boursorama.com\">{{cite web |url=https://www.boursorama.com/actualites/le-secteur-prive-promet-autour-de-700-millions-d-euros-pour-reconstruire-notre-dame-2dd239e4d8c0d278d0c6425acf2a02bc |title=Le secteur priv\u00e9 promet autour de 700 millions d'euros pour reconstruire Notre-Dame |date=16 April 2019 |website=Boursorama |language=fr |agency=Agence France-Presse (AFP)}}</ref>\n* [[Groupe BPCE|BPCE]] (\u20ac10M)<ref name=\"boursorama.com\" />\n}}\n\nThere have been many additional pledges for smaller, or undisclosed, amounts.<ref name=\"anger\">{{cite news |last1=Petrequin |first1=Samuel |title=Anger followed Notre Dame grief for yellow vest protesters |url=https://apnews.com/efb3aba4f029493a9b730d0b532c01bb |work=AP News |date=19 April 2019 |accessdate=22 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190420031730/https://apnews.com/efb3aba4f029493a9b730d0b532c01bb |archive-date=20 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://rs.n1info.com/Vesti/a478180/Vlada-Srbije-uputila-Francuskoj-milion-evra-za-obnovu-katedrale-Notr-Dam.html |title=Vlada Srbije uputila Francuskoj milion evra za obnovu katedrale Notr Dam |website=N1 Srbija |language=sr-Latn |accessdate=22 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190422135412/http://rs.n1info.com/Vesti/a478180/Vlada-Srbije-uputila-Francuskoj-milion-evra-za-obnovu-katedrale-Notr-Dam.html |archive-date=22 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\nA proposal by former minister [[Jean-Jacques Aillagon]] that corporate donations for Notre-Dame should get a 90% tax deduction (rather than the standard 60%) was retracted after public outcry.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Alderman |first1=Liz |last2=Erlanger |first2=Steven |title=As Rich Lavish Cash on Notre-Dame, Many Ask: What About the Needy? |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/17/world/europe/yellow-vest-notre-dame-fire-donations.html |url-access=limited |work=The New York Times |date=17 April 2019 |accessdate=20 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190420191224/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/17/world/europe/yellow-vest-notre-dame-fire-donations.html |archive-date=20 April 2019 |url-status=live |url-access=limited}}</ref> Some donors have said they will not seek tax deductions.<ref name=\"anger\" /> Those who do not pay income tax (more than half of French taxpayers, including many working- and middle-class donors) are not eligible for tax deductions.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Reich |first1=Rob |title=Donors have pledged nearly a billion euros to restore Notre Dame. You may not want to thank them. |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/2019/04/19/donors-have-pledged-nearly-billion-euros-restore-notre-dame-you-may-not-want-thank-them/ |work=The Washington Post |date=19 April 2019 |accessdate=18 May 2019 |url-access=limited}}</ref>\n\nAs of 14 June, only \u20ac80{{nbsp}}million had been collected.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://g1.globo.com/mundo/noticia/2019/06/14/apenas-9percent-das-promessas-de-doacoes-a-notre-dame-foram-cumpridas.ghtml |date=14 June 2019 |title=Only 9% of the donation pledges to Notre-Dame have been fulfilled |work=[[G1 (website)|Global G1]] |accessdate=14 June 2019 |language=pt}}</ref><ref name=\"France24\">{{cite web |url=https://www.france24.com/en/20190614-only-9-millions-pledged-notre-dame-handed-over |date=14 June 2019 |title=Only 9% of millions pledged for Notre-Dame handed over |work=[[France 24]] |accessdate=14 June 2019 |agency=AFP}}</ref> The minister in charge of national museums and monuments, [[Franck Riester]], predicted that further donations would materialise as reconstruction work progressed,<ref name=\"France24\"/> though it was reported that some who made pledges have renounced them because fundraising has been so successful.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.france24.com/en/20190615-paris-notre-dame-cathedral-first-mass-after-devastating-fire-france |date=15 June 2019 |title=Paris's Notre-Dame Cathedral to hold first mass since devastating fire |work=[[France 24]] |accessdate=15 June 2019 |agency=AFP}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[York Minster#1984 fire|1984 York Minster fire]]\n* [[List of building or structure fires]]\n* [[List of destroyed heritage]]\n* [[List of fires at major places of worship]]\n\n== Notes ==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|2019 Notre-Dame de Paris fire}}\n* {{Official website|http://www.notredamedeparis.fr/en|Notre-Dame de Paris}} \u2013 official site\n* [https://www.nga.gov/research/library/imagecollections/features/notre-dame.html Before the Fire: Notre-Dame de Paris in Pictures]\n\n{{Notre-Dame de Paris|state=collapsed}}\n{{Portal bar|Architecture|Catholicism|France}}\n\n[[Category:4th arrondissement of Paris]]\n[[Category:2019 fires in Europe]]\n[[Category:2019 in Christianity]]\n[[Category:2019 in Paris]]\n[[Category:April 2019 events in France]]\n[[Category:Articles containing video clips]]\n[[Category:Building and structure fires in France]]\n[[Category:Building collapses in 2019]]\n[[Category:Fires in Paris]]\n[[Category:Notre-Dame de Paris]]\n[[Category:Paris Fire Brigade]]\n[[Category:Religious buildings and structures fires]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|April 2019 fire at the cathedral of Notre-Dame de Paris, France}}\n{{EngvarB|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox event\n| image                    = NotreDame20190415QuaideMontebello (cropped).jpg\n| image_upright            = 1.3\n| caption                  = Notre-Dame de Paris as seen from Quai de Montebello, {{nobr|with the spire aflame}}\n| map                      = {{location map|Paris#France|label=Notre-Dame Cathedral|lat_deg=48.8530|lon_deg=2.3498|float=center|width=250}}\n| time                     = 18:20 [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]] (16:20 [[UTC]])\n| duration                 = 15 hours<ref>{{cite news |title=Notre-Dame fire: Millions pledged to rebuild cathedral |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-47943705 |website=BBC News |accessdate=17 April 2019 |date=16 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416040109/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-47943705 |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n| date                     = {{start date and age|2019|04|15|df=y}}\n| venue                    = [[Notre-Dame Cathedral]]\n| location                 = Paris\n| coordinates              = {{coord|48.8530|N|2.3498|E|type:landmark_region:FR|display=title,inline}}\n| cause                    = Unknown\n| reported deaths          = 0<ref name=\"gutted\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/live-news/notre-dame-cathedral-fire-extinguished-paris-landmark-gutted-live-updates-04-16-2019/ |title=France vows to rebuild Notre Dame Cathedral after devastating fire |website=CBS News |date=17 April 2019 |accessdate=22 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416092503/https://www.cbsnews.com/live-news/notre-dame-cathedral-fire-extinguished-paris-landmark-gutted-live-updates-04-16-2019/ |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n| reported injuries        = 3<ref name=\"nytimes dontknow\">{{cite news |title=What We Know and Don't Know About the Notre-Dame Fire |work=[[The New York Times]] |date=15 April 2019 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/15/world/europe/notre-dame-fire-what-we-know.html |accessdate=21 July 2019 |url-access=limited}}</ref><ref name=\"cnbc1\" />\n| reported property damage = Roof and spire destroyed; windows and vaulted ceilings damaged\n}}\nOn 15 April 2019, just before 18:20 [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]], a [[structure fire]] broke out beneath the roof of [[Notre-Dame de Paris]] cathedral in Paris. By the time it was extinguished, the building's [[Fl\u00e8che|spire]] and most of its roof had been destroyed and its upper walls severely damaged; extensive damage to the interior was prevented by its stone [[sexpartite vault|vaulted ceiling]], which largely contained the burning roof as it collapsed. Many works of art and religious relics were moved to safety early in the emergency, but others suffered some smoke damage, and some exterior art was damaged or destroyed. The cathedral's [[altar]], two [[pipe organ]]s, and its three 13th-century [[rose window]]s suffered little to no damage. Three emergency workers were injured. Contamination of the site and the nearby environment resulted.<ref name=plume>{{cite news|first1=Elian|last1=Peltier|first2=James|last2=Glanz|first3=Weiyi|last3=Cai|first4=Jeremy|last4=White|url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2019/09/14/world/europe/notre-dame-fire-lead.html|title=Notre-Dame's Toxic Fallout|work=New York Times|date=14 September 2019|access-date=12 April 2020|url-access=limited}}</ref>\n\nFrench president [[Emmanuel Macron]] said that the cathedral would be restored by 2024,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://apnews.com/4f3a963a52ae49fb824d38d55e01d1af |title=The Latest: Fire chaplain hailed as hero in Notre Dame blaze |date=17 April 2019 |website=AP News |language=en-US |access-date=12 April 2020}}</ref> and launched a fundraising campaign which brought in pledges of over \u20ac1{{nbsp}}billion {{as of|2019|04|22|lc=y}}. A complete restoration could require twenty years or more.\n\nOn 25 December 2019, the cathedral did not host Christmas services for the first time since the [[French Revolution]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2019/12/22/notre-dame-fire-no-christmas-mass-first-time-200-years/2726591001/ |title=Notre Dame Cathedral, ravaged by fire in April, will not host Christmas services for first time since French Revolution |last=Bacon |first=John |website=USA Today |language=en-US |access-date=2019-12-26}}</ref>\n{{toclimit|3}}\n\n== Background ==\nThe cathedral of Notre-Dame de Paris (\"Our Lady of Paris\"), part of the \"Paris, Banks of the Seine\" [[UNESCO World Heritage Site]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://whc.unesco.org/en/list/600 |title=Paris, Banks of the Seine |publisher=[[United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization]] (UNESCO) |accessdate=16 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180321014146/https://whc.unesco.org/en/list/600 |archive-date=21 March 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> was begun in the 12th century. Its walls and interior [[vaulted ceiling]] are of stone; its roof and [[fl\u00e8che]] (spire) were of wood (much of it 13th-century oak),<ref name=\"Monde16Avril\">{{cite news |url=https://www.lemonde.fr/les-decodeurs/article/2019/04/16/incendie-de-notre-dame-de-paris-ce-qui-a-ete-perdu-et-ce-qui-a-ete-sauve_5450988_4355770.html |title=Incendie de Notre-Dame de Paris: ce qui a \u00e9t\u00e9 perdu et ce qui a \u00e9t\u00e9 sauv\u00e9 |work=Le Monde |agency=[[Agence France-Presse]] (AFP) |date=16 April 2019 |accessdate=16 April 2019 |language=fr |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416141316/https://www.lemonde.fr/les-decodeurs/article/2019/04/16/incendie-de-notre-dame-de-paris-ce-qui-a-ete-perdu-et-ce-qui-a-ete-sauve_5450988_4355770.html |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=Sasuke |title=Notre-Dame de Paris: toute la charpente en feu, la fl\u00e8che effondr\u00e9e |url=http://maliactu.info/international/notre-dame-de-paris-toute-la-charpente-en-feu-la-fleche-effondree |work=Maliactu |date=15 April 2019 |language=fr |accessdate=16 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416180320/http://maliactu.info/international/notre-dame-de-paris-toute-la-charpente-en-feu-la-fleche-effondree |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> sheathed in lead<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.cnn.com/style/article/nortre-dame-fire-oak-wood-trnd/index.html |title=The entire wooden interior of Notre Dame Cathedral has been lost |first=Ryan |last=Pyror |date=15 April 2019 |accessdate=15 April 2019 |publisher=[[CNN]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190415222810/https://www.cnn.com/style/article/nortre-dame-fire-oak-wood-trnd/index.html |archive-date=15 April 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref> to exclude water.\nThe spire was rebuilt several times, most recently in the 19th century.<ref>{{cite book |accessdate=18 April 2019 |first=Thomas |last=Okey |title=The Story of Paris |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MnlEAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA309& |page=308 |publisher=J.M. Dent & Compan |date=1919 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190420121400/https://books.google.com/books?id=MnlEAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA309& |archive-date=20 April 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |accessdate=16 April 2019 |date=16 April 2019 |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/nation/2019/04/16/story-behind-towering-notre-dame-spire-year-old-architect-commissioned-build-it/ |title=The story behind the towering Notre Dame spire and the 30-year-old architect commissioned to rebuild it |first=Meagan |last=Flynn |work=The Washington Post |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416120744/https://www.washingtonpost.com/nation/2019/04/16/story-behind-towering-notre-dame-spire-year-old-architect-commissioned-build-it/ |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nThe cathedral's stonework has been severely eroded by years of weather and pollution,<ref name=\"cbs undergoing\" /> and the spire had extensively rotted because fissures in its lead sheathing were admitting water.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/decades-of-neglect-threatened-notre-dame-well-before-it-burned-11555624252 |title=Decades of Neglect Threatened Notre Dame, Well Before It Burned |work=[[The Wall Street Journal]] |date=18 April 2019 |accessdate=18 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190418234833/https://www.wsj.com/articles/decades-of-neglect-threatened-notre-dame-well-before-it-burned-11555624252 |archive-date=18 April 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The roof timbers were dry, spongy and powdery with age.<ref name=\"six_questions\" />\nIn 2014, the [[Ministry of Culture (France)|Ministry of Culture]] estimated needed renovations at \u20ac150{{nbsp}}million, and in 2016 the [[Archdiocese of Paris]] launched an appeal to raise \u20ac100{{nbsp}}million over the following five to ten years.\nAt the time of the fire, the spire was undergoing renovation<ref name=\"cbs undergoing\">{{cite web |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/notre-dame-cathedral-fire-notre-dame-68-million-renovation-massive-fire-today/ |title=Notre Dame was undergoing $6.8&nbsp;million renovation when massive fire broke out |date=15 April 2019 |accessdate=15 April 2019 |website=[[CBS News]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190415194731/https://www.cbsnews.com/news/notre-dame-cathedral-fire-notre-dame-68-million-renovation-massive-fire-today/ |archive-date=15 April 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Notre-Dame fire: Blaze breaks out amid renovations at 12th century cathedral |url=https://www.newcivilengineer.com/latest/notre-dame-fire-blaze-breaks-out-amid-renovations-at-12th-century-cathedral/10042011.article |website=New Civil Engineer |accessdate=16 April 2019 |date=15 April 2019 |first=Rob |last=Horgan |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416044826/https://www.newcivilengineer.com/latest/notre-dame-fire-blaze-breaks-out-amid-renovations-at-12th-century-cathedral/10042011.article |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Fire breaks out at top of Notre Dame Cathedral in Paris |url=https://www.independent.ie/world-news/fire-breaks-out-at-top-of-notre-dame-cathedral-in-paris-38017758.html |accessdate=16 April 2019 |work=The Irish Independent |date=15 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416035818/https://www.independent.ie/world-news/fire-breaks-out-at-top-of-notre-dame-cathedral-in-paris-38017758.html |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> and scaffolding had been erected over the [[transept]].<ref name=\"CBC\" /><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.ibtimes.com/notre-dame-cathedral-fire-photos-macron-vows-rebuild-670-year-old-church-2785632 |title=Notre Dame Cathedral Fire Photos: Macron Vows To Rebuild 670-Year Old Church |work=[[International Business Times]] |date=16 April 2019 |accessdate=16 April 2019 |first=Arthur |last=Villasanta |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416060753/https://www.ibtimes.com/notre-dame-cathedral-fire-photos-macron-vows-rebuild-670-year-old-church-2785632 |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nExtensive attention had been given to the risk of fire at the cathedral. The [[Paris Fire Brigade]] drilled regularly to prepare for emergencies there, including on-site exercises in 2018; a firefighter was posted to the cathedral each day; and [[fire warden]]s checked conditions beneath the roof three times daily.<ref name=\"forest\">{{cite news |last1=Breeden |first1=Aurelien |last2=Peltier |first2=Elian |last3=Alderman |first3=Liz |last4=P\u00e9rez-Pe\u00f1a |first4=Richard |title=Notre-Dame Attic Was Known as 'the Forest'. And It Burned Like One. |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/16/world/europe/why-notre-dame-fire-spread.html |url-access=limited |work=The New York Times |date=16 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n{{Gallery\n| title        =Structural elements relevant to the fire\n|mode=packed\n| align        =\n| footer       =\n| style        =padding: 0;\n| state        =\n| height       =250\n| width        =\n| captionstyle =overflow: auto;\n| :File:Notre-Dame de Paris composite transverse section.svg\n | alt1=\n | Timber in reds, stone in blues. Left: tower, with framework and bells; centre (top to bottom, with [[Spire of Notre Dame de Paris|spire]] shown behind): lead roof, timber [[roof truss]]es, stone ceiling vault, nave; right: exterior walls and [[flying buttresses]]. ([[:Commons:File:Notre-Dame de Paris composite transverse section.svg|''Annotations]])\n| File:NOTRE DAME DE PARIS May 2012.jpg\n | alt2=\n | Interior of [[nave]] showing [[rib vault]]ing; in walls are [[clerestory]] windows (top), arches to [[triforium]] (middle), and arches to {{nobr|[[side aisle]]s}} (bottom).\n| File:20130214 - Notre-Dame de Paris - Les nouvelles cloches - 027.jpg\n | alt3=\n | Underside of rib vaulting, whose thrust outward onto the walls is countered by the inward thrust of the flying buttresses. Had the vaulting collapsed, the walls could have collapsed {{nobr|into the nave}}.\n| File:Charpentes Notre Dame 2018 6.jpg\n | alt4=\n | Timber roof framing; vaulted ceiling lies {{nobr|below walkways}}\n| File:\u5723\u6bcd\u9662\u697c\u9876.\u6d82\u9e262 - panoramio.jpg\n | alt5=\n | Lead roof sheathing\n| File:Notre-Dame (41443367785).jpg\n | alt6=\n | Roof and spire. The twelve [[Apostles]] statues at the spire's base had been removed for conservation days before the fire.\n}}\n\n== Fire ==\n[[File:Incendie Notre Dame de Paris cropped.jpg|thumb|upright=0.9|From [[Square Ren\u00e9-Viviani]] at 19:51]]\nFire broke out in the attic beneath the cathedral's roof at 18:18.<ref name=\"nytimes 20190719\">{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2019/07/16/world/europe/notre-dame.html |title=Notre Dame came far closer to collapsing than people knew |first1=Elian |last1=Peltier |first2=James |last2=Glanz |first3=Mika |last3=Gr\u00f6ndahl |first4=Weiji |last4=Kai |first5=Adam |last5=Nossitr |first6=Liza |last6=Alderman |date=17 July 2019 |accessdate=17 July 2019 |work=[[The New York Times]] |url-access=limited}}</ref> At 18:20 the [[fire alarm]] sounded and guards evacuated the cathedral;<ref name=\"minutes\">{{cite news |last1=Hinnant |first1=Lori |title=66 minutes: The frantic race to save Notre Dame |url=https://apnews.com/e9cc2e0e2ce84b7a82abbc23e50bcea1 |work=AP News |date=17 April 2019 |accessdate=22 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416221902/https://apnews.com/e9cc2e0e2ce84b7a82abbc23e50bcea1 |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}} (archive copy legible if javascript turned off)</ref> a guard was sent to investigate, but to the wrong location{{snd}}the attic of the adjoining [[sacristy]]{{snd}}where he found no fire.  About fifteen minutes later the error was discovered, but by the time guards had climbed the three hundred steps to the cathedral attic the fire was well advanced.<ref name=\"nytimes 20190719\"/> The alarm system was not designed to automatically notify the fire brigade, which was summoned at 18:51 after the guards had returned.<ref name=\"nytimes20190419\">{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/19/world/europe/notre-dame-fire-safety.html |title=Notre-Dame's Safety Planners Underestimated the Risk, With Devastating Results |first=Katrin |last=Bennhold |first2=James |last2=Glanz |date=19 April 2019 |work=[[The New York Times]] |accessdate=20 April 2019 |url-access=limited |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190420012938/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/19/world/europe/notre-dame-fire-safety.html |archive-date=20 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\nFirefighters arrived within ten minutes.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-france-notredame-firefighters/paris-firefighters-got-on-notre-dame-site-in-less-than-10-minutes-idUSKCN1RT1N7 |first=Inti |last=Landauro |title=Paris firefighters got on Notre-Dame site in less than 10 minutes |work=Reuters |date=17 April 2017 |accessdate=23 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190418104848/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-france-notredame-firefighters/paris-firefighters-got-on-notre-dame-site-in-less-than-10-minutes-idUSKCN1RT1N7 |archive-date=18 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nPolice evacuated the [[\u00cele de la Cit\u00e9]].<ref name=\"Nossiter\" /><ref name=\"bbc\">{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-47941794 |title=Notre-Dame: Massive fire ravages Paris cathedral |date=16 April 2019 |website=[[BBC News]] |accessdate=22 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416192824/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-47941794 |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://elpais.com/internacional/2019/04/15/actualidad/1555348380_618268.html |title=La catedral de Notre Dame de Par\u00eds sufre un importante incendio |date=15 April 2019 |work=[[El Pa\u00eds]] |accessdate=15 April 2019 |language=es |issn=1134-6582 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190415180838/https://elpais.com/internacional/2019/04/15/actualidad/1555348380_618268.html |archive-date=15 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> White smoke rising from the roof<ref name=\"Nossiter\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/15/world/europe/notre-dame-fire.html |title=Notre-Dame Cathedral in Paris Catches Fire |last=Nossiter |first=Adam |date=15 April 2019 |work=The New York Times |accessdate=15 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190415174607/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/15/world/europe/notre-dame-fire.html |archive-date=15 April 2019 |url-status=live |last2=Breeden |first2=Aurelien |issn=0362-4331 |url-access=limited}}</ref> turned black before flames appeared from the spire, [[Backdraft|then turned yellow]].<ref name=\"Nossiter\" /><ref>{{cite news |title=Massive fire engulfs beloved Notre Dame Cathedral in Paris |url=https://apnews.com/73404d09773740f699d4b92933abec50 |website=AP News |date=15 April 2019 |accessdate=16 April 2019 |first1=Lori |last1=Hinnant |first2=Samuel |last2=Petrequin |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190415175914/https://apnews.com/73404d09773740f699d4b92933abec50 |archive-date=15 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== Firefighting ===\n[[File:Fl\u00e8che en feu - Spire on Fire.jpeg|thumb|left|upright=0.65|The spire aflame]]\n[[File:NDonFire 8773 (edited).jpg|thumb|upright=1.2|Firefighters using a [[deluge gun]]]]\nMore than 400 firefighters were engaged;<ref name=\"hard\" /> another hundred{{clarify|reason=firefighters or all people? sources contradictory?|date=July 2019}} worked to move precious objects to safety via [[Bucket brigade|a human chain]]<ref name=\"forest\" /> also including police and municipal workers.<ref name=\"reuters damage\" />\n\nThe fire was primarily fought from inside the structure, which was more dangerous for personnel but reduced potential damage to the cathedral; applying water from outside risked deflecting flames and hot gases (at temperatures up to 800{{nbsp}}\u00b0C or 1500{{nbsp}}\u00b0F) inwards.<ref name=\"six_questions\">{{cite web |url=http://www.leparisien.fr/faits-divers/six-questions-sur-l-incendie-de-notre-dame-de-paris-15-04-2019-8054094.php |title=Six questions sur l'incendie de Notre-Dame de Paris |trans-title=Six questions about the fire of Notre-Dame |website=Le Parisien |date=16 April 2019 |accessdate=16 April 2019 |language=fr |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416005330/http://www.leparisien.fr/faits-divers/six-questions-sur-l-incendie-de-notre-dame-de-paris-15-04-2019-8054094.php |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live |first1=Jean-Michel |last1=D\u00e9cugis |first2=Vincent |last2=Gautronneau |first3=J\u00e9r\u00e9mie |last3=Pham-L\u00ea}}</ref> [[Deluge gun]]s<ref name=\"hard\">{{cite news |url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/04/15/europe/firefighters-notre-dame-intl/ |first=Joshua |last=Berlinger |title=Why the Notre Dame fire was so hard to put out |website=CNN |date=16 April 2019 |accessdate=24 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190417103658/https://www.cnn.com/2019/04/15/europe/firefighters-notre-dame-intl/ |archive-date=17 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.cnn.com/world/live-news/notre-dame-fire/h_c29f6d43801da4f0b308b45e8665efe1 |title=400 firefighters mobilized for Notre Dame blaze |date=15 April 2019 |website=CNN |accessdate=15 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.newschannel5.com/news/world/notre-dame-cathedral-in-paris-is-on-fire-reports-say |title=Fire at Notre Dame Cathedral under control; firefighters have saved cathedral's towers |date=15 April 2019 |website=NewsChannel5 Nashville |accessdate=15 April 2019 |agency=CNN}}</ref> were used at lower-than-usual pressures to minimise damage to the cathedral and its contents.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/how-paris-firefighters-saved-notre-dame-11555540386 |url-access=subscription |title=How Paris Firefighters Helped Preserve Notre Dame Towers |first1=Sam |last1=Schechner |first2=Nick |last2=Kostov |date=17 April 2019 |work=The Wall Street Journal |accessdate=18 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190418193228/https://www.wsj.com/articles/how-paris-firefighters-saved-notre-dame-11555540386 |archive-date=18 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\nWater was supplied by pump-boat from the [[Seine]].<ref name=\"forest\" /><!--Deliberate ambiguity, as some more recent sources seem to have only one pump-boat-->\n\n[[Aerial firefighting]] was not used because water dropped from heights could have done structural damage, and heated stone can crack if suddenly cooled.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/live/2019/apr/15/notre-dame-cathedral-fire-paris-france-landmark-live-news |title=Cathedral fire under control after spire and roof destroyed \u2013 as it happened |work=The Guardian |accessdate=16 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=How Catastrophic Is the Notre-Dame Cathedral Fire? |url=https://www.citylab.com/design/2019/04/notre-dame-cathedral-fire-paris-gothic-architecture-history/587191/ |work=CityLab |date=15 April 2019 |first1=Kriston |last1=Capps |first2=Feargus |last2=O'Sullivan |accessdate=16 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416043321/https://www.citylab.com/design/2019/04/notre-dame-cathedral-fire-paris-gothic-architecture-history/587191/ |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> Helicopters were not used because of dangerous [[updraft]]s<ref name=\"hard\" /> but drones were used for visual and [[thermal imaging]], and robots for visual imaging and directing water streams.<ref name=\"forest\" /><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.techtimes.com/articles/241710/20190417/french-firefighting-robot-colossus-helped-save-burning-notre-dame-cathedral.htm |title=French Firefighting Robot Colossus Helped Save Burning Notre Dame Cathedral |last=Navarro |first=Alyssa |date=17 April 2019 |website=Tech Times |accessdate=17 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190417162330/https://www.techtimes.com/articles/241710/20190417/french-firefighting-robot-colossus-helped-save-burning-notre-dame-cathedral.htm |archive-date=17 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> Molten lead falling from the roof posed a special hazard for firefighters.<ref name=\"Nossiter\" />\n\nBy 18:52, smoke was visible from outside; flames appeared in the next ten minutes, as firefighters arrived. The spire of the cathedral collapsed at 19:50, creating a draft that slammed all the doors and sent a fireball through the attic. Firefighters then retreated from within the attic. Shortly before the spire fell, the fire had spread to the wooden framework inside the north tower, which supported [[Notre-Dame de Paris#Bells|eight very large bells]]. Had the bells fallen, it was thought that the damage done as they fell could have collapsed the towers, and with them the entire cathedral. At 20:30, firefighters abandoned attempts to extinguish the roof and concentrated on saving the towers, fighting from within and between the towers. By 21:45 the fire was under control.<ref name=\"nytimes 20190719\" />\n\nAdjacent apartment buildings were evacuated due to concern about possible collapse,<ref name=\"forest\" /> but on 19 April the fire brigade ruled out that risk.<ref name=\"april19rescue\">{{cite news |url=https://www.apnews.com/92db19558da04f09b94cc31fb5ce16a5 |title=Fire-ravaged Notre Dame now stabilized, firefighters leave |first1=Nicolas |last1=Vaux-Montagny |first2=Sylvie |last2=Corbet |website=AP News |date=19 April 2019 |accessdate=20 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190420011833/https://apnews.com/92db19558da04f09b94cc31fb5ce16a5 |archive-date=20 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> One firefighter and two police officers were injured.<ref name=\"nytimes dontknow\" /><ref name=\"cnbc1\">{{cite web |url=https://www.cnbc.com/2019/04/15/paris-notre-dame-cathedral-on-fire-reuters.html |title=Notre Dame will be rebuilt within the next five years, French President Emmanuel Macron says |last1=El-Bawab |first1=Nadine |last2=Newburger |first2=Emma |last3=Steinberg |first3=Marty |date=16 April 2019 |publisher=[[CNBC]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190418202153/https://www.cnbc.com/2019/04/15/paris-notre-dame-cathedral-on-fire-reuters.html |archive-date=18 April 2019 |url-status=live |accessdate=23 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Damage ===\n{{further|Spire of Notre-Dame de Paris}}\n[[File:Notre-Dame-Fire.gif|thumb|right|upright=1.2|Animation showing the south facade before and after the fire; scaffolding had been erected as part of renovations underway when the fire started.]]\n[[File:Paris and environs with routes from London to Paris handbook for travellers (1913) eingenordet.png|thumb|upright=1.2|The area directly under the [[Crossing (architecture)|crossing]] and two other cells of vaulting collapsed]]\n[[File:Notre Dame de Paris roof damage aerial.webm|thumb|The roof reduced to piles of char atop the mostly-intact vaults]]\nMost of the wood/metal roof and the spire of the cathedral was destroyed, with about one third of the roof remaining.<ref name=\"Nossiter\" /> The remnants of the roof and spire fell atop the stone vault underneath, which forms the ceiling of the cathedral's interior.<ref name=\"intact_vault\">{{cite web |last1=Lapin |first1=Tamar |title=Photos show center of Notre Dame cathedral miraculously intact |url=https://nypost.com/2019/04/15/photos-show-center-of-notre-dame-cathedral-miraculously-intact/ |website=New York Post |date=15 April 2019 |accessdate=16 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416032930/https://nypost.com/2019/04/15/photos-show-center-of-notre-dame-cathedral-miraculously-intact/ |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cnn.com/style/article/nortre-dame-fire-oak-wood-trnd/index.html |title=The entire wooden interior of Notre Dame Cathedral has been destroyed |first=Ryan |last=Prior |date=15 April 2019 |publisher=CNN |accessdate=16 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190415222810/https://www.cnn.com/style/article/nortre-dame-fire-oak-wood-trnd/index.html |archive-date=15 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> Some sections of this vaulting collapsed in turn,<ref name=\"intact_vault\" /> allowing debris from the burning roof to fall to the marble floor below,<ref name=\"minutes\" /> but most sections remained intact due to the use of [[rib vault]]ing, greatly reducing damage to the cathedral's interior and objects within.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.latimes.com/opinion/op-ed/la-oe-goodheart-notre-dame-fire-gothic-20190417-story.html |first=Adam |last=Goodheart |title=Who saved Notre Dame? Its builders |date=17 April 2019 |work=Los Angeles Times |department=Op-Ed |accessdate=23 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190423213709/https://www.latimes.com/opinion/op-ed/la-oe-goodheart-notre-dame-fire-gothic-20190417-story.html |archive-date=23 April 2019 |url-status=live |url-access=limited}}</ref>\n\nThe cathedral contained a large number of artworks, religious relics, and other irreplaceable treasures,<ref name=\"contents\" /> including a [[Crown of thorns#France|crown of thorns]] said to be the one Jesus wore at his crucifixion, a purported [[True Cross|piece of the cross]] on which Jesus was crucified, the [[Louis IX of France#Religious nature|Tunic of St. Louis]],<ref>{{cite news |title=Notre Dame crown of thorns and St Louis tunic saved from cathedral fire |url=https://metro.co.uk/2019/04/16/notre-dame-crown-thorns-st-louis-tunic-saved-cathedral-fire-9219579/ |newspaper=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]] |date=16 April 2019 |accessdate=16 April 2019 |df=dmy-all |first=Richard |last=Hartley-Parkinson |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416135729/https://metro.co.uk/2019/04/16/notre-dame-crown-thorns-st-louis-tunic-saved-cathedral-fire-9219579/ |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Buncombe\" /> a [[Notre-Dame de Paris#Organ|much-rebuilt]] pipe organ by [[Aristide Cavaill\u00e9-Coll]], and the 14th-century [[Virgin of Paris]] statue.<ref name=\"contents\">{{cite web |url=https://www.sfgate.com/news/article/art-destroyed-in-fire-notre-dame-paris-artifacts-13769096.php |title=What's inside the Notre Dame Cathedral in Paris |last=Martichoux |first=Alix |date=15 April 2019 |website=San Francisco Chronicle |accessdate=15 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190415211841/https://www.sfgate.com/news/article/art-destroyed-in-fire-notre-dame-paris-artifacts-13769096.php |archive-date=15 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nSome artwork had been removed in preparation for the renovations, and most of the cathedral's sacred relics were held in the adjoining sacristy, which the fire did not reach; all the cathedral's relics survived.<ref name=\"april19rescue\" /><ref>{{cite web |first=Thomas |last=Adamson |url=http://www.startribune.com/drunk-on-smoke-notre-dame-s-bees-survive-cathedral-blaze/508801942/ |title=Drunk on smoke: Notre Dame's bees survive cathedral blaze |work=[[Star Tribune]] |agency=Associated Press |date=19 April 2019 |accessdate=19 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190419144702/http://www.startribune.com/drunk-on-smoke-notre-dame-s-bees-survive-cathedral-blaze/508801942/ |archive-date=19 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/europe/pariss-notre-cathedral-is-on-fire/2019/04/15/c487906e-5fa1-11e9-bf24-db4b9fb62aa2_story.html |title=Notre Dame Cathedral spire collapses as Paris monument is consumed by fire |last1=McAuley |first1=James |last2=Whitt |first2=Griff |date=15 April 2019 |work=[[The Washington Post]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190415184931/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/europe/pariss-notre-cathedral-is-on-fire/2019/04/15/c487906e-5fa1-11e9-bf24-db4b9fb62aa2_story.html |archive-date=15 April 2019 |url-status=live |accessdate=15 April 2019}}</ref> Some contents were moved by a human chain of emergency workers and civil servants.<ref name=\"reuters damage\" /> Many valuables that were not removed also survived, but the state of many others remained unknown as of 16 April.<ref name=\"Monde16Avril\" />{{Update inline|date=March 2020}}\n\n[[came|Lead joints]] in some of the 19th-century stained-glass windows melted,<ref name=\"nytimes cot\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/15/world/europe/crown-of-thorns-notre-dame.html |title=Notre-Dame: Fate of Priceless Cultural Treasures Uncertain |last=Marshall |first=Alex |date=15 April 2019 |work=The New York Times |accessdate=16 April 2019 |last2=Stack |first2=Liam |issn=0362-4331 |last3=Murphy |first3=Heather |url-access=limited |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416070310/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/15/world/europe/crown-of-thorns-notre-dame.html |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> but the three major rose windows, dating to the 13th century, were undamaged. One weakened window may need to be dismantled for safekeeping.{{update inline|date=June 2019}}<ref>{{cite news |last1=Guyonnet |first1=Paul |title=Notre-Dame: Les vitraux des rosaces ont surv\u00e9cu \u00e0 l'incendie |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.fr/entry/notre-dame-vitraux-rosaces-incendie_fr_5cb58dece4b082aab08b55e0 |accessdate=16 April 2019 |work=[[The Huffington Post]] |location=Notre-Dame |date=16 April 2019 |language=fr |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416123535/https://www.huffingtonpost.fr/entry/notre-dame-vitraux-rosaces-incendie_fr_5cb58dece4b082aab08b55e0 |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.newsweek.com/notre-dame-rose-windows-fire-paris-cathedral-1397773 |title=Notre Dame 'miracle'? Rose windows' stained glass appears to have survived savage blaze |first=Katherine |last=Hignett |date=16 April 2019 |website=[[Newsweek]] |accessdate=17 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416143859/https://www.newsweek.com/notre-dame-rose-windows-fire-paris-cathedral-1397773 |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-france-notredame-patrimony-idUSKCN1RS1IF |work=Reuters |title=Notre-Dame's famed rose window spared but blaze harms priceless artworks |first1=Sarah |last1=White |first2=Elizabeth |last2=Pineau |date=16 April 2019 |accessdate=17 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416221222/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-france-notredame-patrimony-idUSKCN1RS1IF |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> Several pews were destroyed and the [[Vault (architecture)|vaulted arches]] were blackened by smoke, though the church's main cross and altar survived, along with the statues surrounding it.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thelocal.fr/20190416/like-a-nightmare-hundreds-of-parisians-gather-to-witness-destruction-at-notre-dame |title='The church is burning and the whole world is crying' \u2013 Parisians mourn for Notre-Dame |work=[[The Local]] |date=16 April 2019 |accessdate=20 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190417135343/https://www.thelocal.fr/20190416/like-a-nightmare-hundreds-of-parisians-gather-to-witness-destruction-at-notre-dame |archive-date=17 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.yahoo.com/notre-dame-counts-cost-daylight-reveals-damage-092808310.html |title=Notre-Dame counts cost as daylight reveals damage |work=Yahoo! News |agency=Agence France-Presse (AFP) |date=16 April 2019 |accessdate=16 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416190208/https://news.yahoo.com/notre-dame-counts-cost-daylight-reveals-damage-092808310.html |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nSome paintings, apparently only smoke-damaged,<ref name=\"nytimes cot\"/> are expected to be transported to the [[Louvre]] for restoration. A number of statues, including those of the twelve Apostles at the base of the spire, had been removed in preparation for renovations.<ref name=\"CBC\">{{cite news |url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/world/notre-dame-cathedral-paris-fire-1.5098604 |title=Notre-Dame Cathedral spire in Paris collapses, engulfed in flames |agency=[[Reuters]] |publisher=[[CBC News]] |date=15 April 2019 |accessdate=15 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190415181728/https://www.cbc.ca/news/world/notre-dame-cathedral-paris-fire-1.5098604 |archive-date=15 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Buncombe\">{{cite news |last1=Buncombe |first1=Andrew |title=Notre Dame's historic statues safe after being removed just days before massive fire |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/notre-dame-cathedral-fire-statues-renovation-apostles-evangelists-a8871586.html |accessdate=15 April 2019 |work=The Independent |date=15 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190415195451/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/notre-dame-cathedral-fire-statues-renovation-apostles-evangelists-a8871586.html |archive-date=15 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\nThe rooster-shaped [[reliquary]] atop the spire was found damaged but intact among the debris.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rtl.fr/actu/justice-faits-divers/le-coq-de-la-fleche-de-notre-dame-de-paris-retrouve-7797444660 |title=Le coq de la fl\u00e8che a \u00e9t\u00e9 retrouv\u00e9 |website=RTL |agency=[[Agence France-Presse]] (AFP) |language=fr |first=Thomas |last=Pierre |date=16 April 2019 |accessdate=16 April 2019}}</ref>\nThe three pipe organs were not significantly damaged.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.europe1.fr/societe/exclusif-lorgue-principal-de-notre-dame-de-paris-miraculeusement-preserve-rien-na-brule-rien-na-fondu-3892910 |title=L'orgue principal de Notre-Dame de Paris miraculeusement pr\u00e9serv\u00e9 |date=16 April 2019 |publisher=[[Europe 1]] |accessdate=16 April 2019 |language=fr |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416094748/https://www.europe1.fr/societe/exclusif-lorgue-principal-de-notre-dame-de-paris-miraculeusement-preserve-rien-na-brule-rien-na-fondu-3892910 |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/24/arts/music/notre-dame-organ-fire.html |title=Notre-Dame Musicians Rejoice That Cathedral's Organ Was Spared |last=Marshall |first=Alex |date=24 April 2019 |work=The New York Times |accessdate=24 April 2019 |issn=0362-4331 |url-access=limited}}</ref> The largest of the cathedral's bells, the [[Bourdon (bell)|bourdon]], was not damaged.<ref name=\"Monde16Avril\" /> The liturgical treasury of the cathedral and the \"grands [[May (painting)|Mays]]\" paintings were moved to safety.<ref name=\"Monde16Avril\" />\n\n==== Environmental damage ====\n[[Airparif]] said winds rapidly dispersed the smoke, carrying it away aloft along the Seine corridor. It did not find elevated levels of particulate air pollution at monitoring stations nearby.<ref>{{cite web |title=Incendie de Notre-Dame de Paris: point sur la situation |url=https://www.paris.fr/notre-dame |website=paris.fr |language=fr |accessdate=20 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190420192759/https://www.paris.fr/notre-dame |archive-date=20 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Incendie de Notre-Dame : le feu a-t-il pollu\u00e9 l\u2019air de Paris ? |url=http://www.leparisien.fr/societe/incendie-de-notre-dame-le-feu-a-t-il-pollue-l-air-de-paris-16-04-2019-8054682.php |website=leparisien.fr |language=fr-FR |date=16 April 2019}}</ref> The Paris police have stated that there was no danger from breathing the air around the fire.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Chrisafis |first1=Angelique |title=Notre Dame fire: police say air not toxic despite high lead levels on ground |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/may/09/paris-police-say-no-danger-of-toxic-inhalation-from-air-near-notre-dame |website=The Guardian |date=9 May 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe burned-down roof was covered with over 400 metric [[tons]] of [[lead (metal)|lead]].<ref name=plume/><!--the NYT seriously did not specify what sort of 460 tons--><ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://time.com/5638584/notre-dame-lead-poisoning/ |author=Billy Perrigo |title=Notre Dame Fire: Environmental Group Files Lead Poisoning Lawsuit |magazine=Time |date=30 July 2019 |accessdate=13 August 2019}}</ref> Settling dust substantially raised surface lead levels in some places nearby,<ref>{{cite web |title=Blood tests recommended over Notre Dame lead risk |url=https://apnews.com/33a616f0a5d844578b425d806f4fb362 |website=AP NEWS |accessdate=7 August 2019 |date=4 June 2019}}</ref> notably the cordoned-off area and places left open during the fire.<ref>{{cite web |title=Information aux riverains et aux personnes travaillant aux abords de la cath\u00e9drale Notre-Dame de Paris |url=http://www.prefectures-regions.gouv.fr/ile-de-france/content/download/57788/379997/file/CP%20PP%2027042019%20-%20Information%20aux%20riverains%20de%20Notre-Dame.pdf |website=[prefectures-regions.gouv.fr/ile-de-france Prefecture of Paris website] |publisher=[[Prefecture of Paris]] |date=27 April 2019}}</ref> Wet cleaning for surfaces<ref>{{cite web |title=Officials warn of lead pollution risks after Notre-Dame blaze |url=https://phys.org/news/2019-05-notre-dame-roof-astronomical.html |website=phys.org |language=en-us |date=9 May 2019}}</ref> and blood tests for children and pregnant women were recommended in the immediate area.<ref>{{cite web |last1=France-Presse |first1=Agence |title=Children and pregnant women around Notre Dame warned over lead |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/jun/04/notre-dame-lead-levels-in-blood |website=The Guardian |date=4 June 2019}}</ref> People working on the cathedral after the fire did not initially take the lead precautions required for their own protection; materials leaving the site were decontaminated, but some clothing was not, and some precautions were not correctly followed; as a result, the worksite failed some inspections and was temporarily shut down.<ref name=plume/><ref>{{cite web |last1=Kovacs |first1=St\u00e9phane |title=Notre-Dame de Paris : le chantier suspendu \u00e0 cause du plomb |url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/actualite-france/le-chantier-de-notre-dame-suspendu-pour-plusieurs-jours-par-mesure-de-precaution-20190725 |website=Le Figaro |date=25 July 2019}}</ref> There was also more widespread contamination; testing, cleanup, and public health advisories were delayed for months, and the neighbourhood was not decontaminated for four months, prompting widespread criticism.<ref name=plume/>\n\nAverage lead levels in Paris streets are normally five times the indoor legal limit (1000 [[microgram|\u03bcg]]/m<sup>2</sup>), due to historic uses of lead,<ref>{{cite news |title=The Notre Dame Fire Spread Toxic Lead Dust Over Paris |url=https://www.wired.com/story/the-notre-dame-fire-spread-toxic-lead-dust-over-paris/ |website=Wired |date=1 August 2019 |accessdate=3 August 2019 |last1=O'Sullivan |first1=Feargus}}</ref> principally from runoff from intact roofs.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Robert |first1=Pauline |last2=Gromaire |first2=Marie-Christine |last3=de Gouvello |first3=Bernard |last4=Chebbo |first4=Ghassan |title=IMPACT DES MAT\u00c9RIAUX DE TOITURES SUR LA CONTAMINATION M\u00c9TALLIQUE DES EAUX DE RUISSELLEMENT URBAINES |conference=17\u00e8mes Journ\u00e9es Scientifiques de l\u2019Environnement: le citoyen, la ville et l\u2019environnement |date=May 2006 |url=https://hal.archives-ouvertes.fr/hal-00182628/document}}</ref> The Health Ministry rules that children should not be exposed to more than 70 micrograms/m<sup>2</sup> indoors. There is no legal limit for outdoor lead levels, which are often very heterogeneous; the L'Agence r\u00e9gionale de sant\u00e9 (ARS) d'Ile-de-France is not certain if some of the elevated levels being measured are connected to the fire.<ref>{{cite web |title=Plomb de Notre-Dame: l'Agence r\u00e9gionale de sant\u00e9 se veut rassurante |url=https://www.lefigaro.fr/plomb-de-notre-dame-l-agence-regionale-de-sante-se-veut-rassurante-20190704 |website=Le Figaro |date=4 July 2019 |agency=AFP}}</ref> This lack of clarity and threshold-linked mandatory measures may have delayed action. In mid-July, regional health officials raised their outdoor guideline from 1000 [[micrograms]]/m<sup>2</sup> to 5000.<ref name=plume/><!--93 to 464 \"micrograms per square foot\", but 70mcg/m2 limit given in original metric units. The NYT is apparently making the transition to metric units gradually...--> Rain can redistribute the lead dust.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Willsher |first1=Kim |title=Notre Dame firefighters should be tested for lead, say campaigners |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/may/10/notre-dame-firefighters-should-be-tested-for-lead-say-campaigners |website=The Guardian |date=10 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Reactions ===\n[[File:Hommage_sauveteurs_ND2.jpg|thumb|upleft=1.2|left|Plaque in front of the [[H\u00f4tel de Ville, Paris|H\u00f4tel de Ville]] in homage to the cathedral and those who helped save it]]<!-- not sure this is needed; if so, it should probably be cropped to the billboard, not the statue-->\nMacron, postponing a speech to address the [[yellow vests movement]] planned for that evening,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://apnews.com/e4f5f49d9f2d46348cdda1d86ea8a41e |title=France's Macron requests post-fire pause from politics |website=AP News |date=16 April 2019 |accessdate=23 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190423215533/https://apnews.com/e4f5f49d9f2d46348cdda1d86ea8a41e |archive-date=23 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> went to Notre Dame and gave a brief address there.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/macron-postpones-speech-after-notre-dame-fire/ |title=Notre Dame fire 'fully extinguished' as fundraising starts |first1=Rym |last1=Momtaz |first2=Laurenz |last2=Gehrke |date=16 April 2019 |website=[[Politico]] |accessdate=23 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190420085901/https://www.politico.eu/article/macron-postpones-speech-after-notre-dame-fire/ |archive-date=20 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> Numerous world religious{{efn|The [[Holy See|Vatican]],<ref name=\"ap-latest\" /> and the Presiding Bishop of [[The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thechurchnews.com/global/2019-04-15/notre-dame-fire-flames-paris-holy-week-hope-jesus-christ-49533 |title=Hope from ashes: Why the Notre Dame fire is a symbol of rebirth during Holy Week |date=15 April 2019 |first=Aubrey |last=Eyre |work=[[Church News]] |accessdate=16 April 2019 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/77gAjb66T?url=https://www.thechurchnews.com/global/2019-04-15/notre-dame-fire-flames-paris-holy-week-hope-jesus-christ-49533 |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>{{third-party inline|date=March 2020}} among many others.{{cn|date=March 2020}}|name=|}} and government leaders{{efn|Including Prime Minister of Italy [[Giuseppe Conte]],<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/19_aprile_15/incendio-notre-dame-sgomento-mondo-24339856-5fb0-11e9-b974-356c261cf349.shtml |title=Incendio Notre Dame, lo sgomento del mondo: \"Brucia una parte di noi\" |date=15 April 2019 |newspaper=[[Corriere della Sera]] |accessdate=23 April 2019}}</ref> Secretary-General of the United Nations [[Ant\u00f3nio Guterres]],<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.cnn.com/world/live-news/notre-dame-fire/h_a431aa2b54dabf7572cc175ef81500db |title=UN chief: 'Horrified by the pictures coming from Paris' |date=15 April 2019 |publisher=[[CNN]] |accessdate=15 April 2019}}</ref> President of the European Council [[Donald Tusk]],<ref>{{cite tweet |user=eucopresident |number=1117848950742978560 |title=Notre-Dame de Paris est Notre-Dame de toute l'Europe. We are all with Paris today. |first=Donald |last=Tusk |authorlink=Donald Tusk |language=fr |date=15 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.euractiv.com/section/politics/news/we-are-all-with-paris-today-international-sorrow-as-fire-ravages-notre-dame-in-paris/ |date=16 April 2019 |title='We are all with Paris today': International sorrow as fire ravages Notre-Dame |work=[[EURACTIV]] |accessdate=19 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190417104748/https://www.euractiv.com/section/politics/news/we-are-all-with-paris-today-international-sorrow-as-fire-ravages-notre-dame-in-paris/ |archive-date=17 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> President of the European Commission [[Jean-Claude Juncker]],<ref>{{cite 