Slovenia]], [[Portugal]], and [[Turkey]]. In January 2011 it became Duck TV.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rapidtvnews.com/index.php/201101209885/bebetv-turns-into-ducktv.html |title=bebeTV turns into ducktv |author=J\u00f6rn Krieger |date=2011-01-20 |publisher=Rapid TV News |accessdate=19 May 2011}}</ref>\n\n==ducktv Series==\n* ''[[Africa]]''\n* ''[[Animals]]''\n* ''[[Dinoland]]''\n* ''[[Doll Team]]''\n* ''[[Fireteam]]''\n* ''Get Up!''\n* ''Holiday''\n* ''[[Hop-hop]]''\n* ''Indi''\n* ''[[India]]''\n* ''[[Leon-ART]]''\n* ''[[Mimo and Bobo]]''\n* ''[[Monica and Rudy 2]]''\n* ''[[Monica and Rudy]]''\n* ''Ogan''\n* ''[[Risto Gusto]]''\n* ''[[Roleplay]]''\n* ''[[Sounds of Dreams]]''\n* ''[[Sunville]]''\n* ''The Sweet Life''\n* ''[[Tangram]]''\n* ''[[Vege-tales]]''\n* ''[[The World of Animals]]''\n* ''[[Zoo]]''\n\n== ducktv Sections ==\n* ''Bedtime Stories''\n* ''[[ducktv Favorites]]''\n* ''[[Fall on ducktv]]''\n* ''[[Learn With ducktv]]''\n* ''[[Let's Move]]''\n* ''Sleep Tight''\n* ''[[Spring on ducktv]]''\n* ''[[Summer on ducktv]]''\n* ''[[Winter on ducktv]]''\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://www.ducktv.tv/ Official site]\n\n{{Television in Romania}}\n\n[[Category:Television channels and stations established in 2007]]\n[[Category:Children's television networks]]\n\n{{tv-station-stub}}\n{{europe-tv-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{Refimprove|date=May 2011}}\n{{COI|date=May 2011}}\n}}\n{{Infobox TV channel\n| name = Duck TV\n| logofile = ducktv-logo.jpg\n| logosize = 125px\n| logoalt =\n| logo2 =\n| launch = October 2007<br /> September 2012 (Problem)\n| share =0.2%\n| share as of =\n| share source =\n| closed date =\n| picture format =\n| network =\n| owner = Mega Max Media s.r.o.\n| slogan = Television for absolute beginners\n| country = [[Slovakia]]\n| broadcast area = International\n| headquarters =\n| former names = Bebe TV (2007\u20132011)\n| replaced names =\n| replaced by names =\n| sister names =\n| timeshift name